%global packname  placer
%global packver   0.1.3
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.1.3
Release:          2%{?dist}
Summary:          PLastic ACcumulation Estimate using R (PLACER)

License:          MIT + file LICENSE
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel >= 3.5.0
Requires:         R-core >= 3.5.0
BuildArch:        noarch

%description
Assessment of the prevalence of plastic debris in bird nests based on
bootstrap replicates. The package allows for calculating bootstrapped 95%
confidence intervals for the estimated prevalence of debris. Combined with
a Bayesian approach, the resampling simulations can be also used to define
appropriate sample sizes to detect prevalence of plastics. The method has
wide application, and can also be applied to estimate confidence intervals
and define sample sizes for the prevalence of plastics ingested by any
other organisms. The method is described in Tavares et al. (Submitted).

